From 1a0004000000000000000000000000000000ob04 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: OpenBook Maintainers <goodhackersolutions@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 8 Jun 2026 00:00:03 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 4/6] privacy: stop building the Pocket component

SPDX-License-Identifier: MPL-2.0

Pocket is a remote service (getpocket.com) with no place in a zero-egress
privacy browser. The AutoConfig locks extensions.pocket.enabled=false and
policies.json sets DisablePocket=true, but those only disable it at runtime.
This patch stops the Pocket built-in component from being compiled/registered
at all, so the code and its endpoints are not even present in the build.

Cross-refs:
  - config/autoconfig/openbook.cfg  -> lockPref("extensions.pocket.enabled", false)
  - config/policies/policies.json   -> "DisablePocket": true

NOTE: the exact build-config gate for Pocket drifts across Firefox versions;
rebased in CI against Firefox 145.0.2 (see patches/README.md).
---
 browser/components/moz.build | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/browser/components/moz.build b/browser/components/moz.build
index 7777777..8888888 100644
--- a/browser/components/moz.build
+++ b/browser/components/moz.build
@@ -40,6 +40,6 @@ DIRS += [
     "newtab",
     "places",
-    "pocket",
+    # OpenBook: "pocket" removed -- the getpocket.com built-in is not compiled.
     "preferences",
     "privatebrowsing",
     "protections",
--
2.45.0
